messages.text:
The current information available suggests that the Vice President of the United States (VPOTUS) is the second-highest ranking official in the executive branch of the US Government, after the President of the United States. They hold a position equivalent to the Deputy Prime Minister in many countries around the world, but with fewer duties and responsibilities. As such, their role is primarily ceremonial and symbolic in nature, rather than having any real power or authority within the administration. However, they do play a significant role in ensuring the smooth functioning of government and maintaining public trust
